# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: MariusPath
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "When Sarah woke the next morning, the day unfolded, same as before."
    new "When Sarah woke the next morning, the day unfolded, same as before."

    old "She rose with the others, made breakfast, send Marius on his way early, and took the house work."
    new "She rose with the others, made breakfast, send Marius on his way early, and took the house work."

    old "Sarah was surprised to learn that even in so small a household, the daily work required to maintain it was almost a full job."
    new "Sarah was surprised to learn that even in so small a household, the daily work required to maintain it was almost a full job."

    old "After finishing up the remainder of the laundry that she had not been able to get to the day before, she took to cleaning up inside the home."
    new "After finishing up the remainder of the laundry that she had not been able to get to the day before, she took to cleaning up inside the home."

    old "The two men had lived rather practically before she arrived, and cleanliness was a distant consideration."
    new "The two men had lived rather practically before she arrived, and cleanliness was a distant consideration."

    old "Sarah imagined that now she was here, at the very least, she could add a feminine touch."
    new "Sarah imagined that now she was here, at the very least, she could add a feminine touch."

    old "She headed back into the yard and began to walk the perimeter, marked by the ramshackle fence."
    new "She headed back into the yard and began to walk the perimeter, marked by the ramshackle fence."

    old "It was a sizeable plot, she realized."
    new "It was a sizeable plot, she realized."

    old "A large oak tree, some small garden plots for various vegetables. A dilapidated barn that housed a few animals."
    new "A large oak tree, some small garden plots for various vegetables. A dilapidated barn that housed a few animals."

    old "Animals and Marius' father, Alfred."
    new "Animals and Marius' father, Alfred."

    old "An animal of a different sort, she concluded."
    new "An animal of a different sort, she concluded."

    old "Out near the far eastern edge of the plot, she found a patch of flowers, growing in between the fence posts."
    new "Out near the far eastern edge of the plot, she found a patch of flowers, growing in between the fence posts."

    old "Kneeling down, Sarah carefully studied the flowers."
    new "Kneeling down, Sarah carefully studied the flowers."

    old "In castle Reinmeer, she had always loved flowers and plants. The royal garden had been especially precious to her."
    new "In castle Reinmeer, she had always loved flowers and plants. The royal garden had been especially precious to her."

    old "But now it struck her how different these flowers were."
    new "But now it struck her how different these flowers were."

    old "Here they lacked the disciplined hands of the dozen gardeners that carefully managed and treated each specimen."
    new "Here they lacked the disciplined hands of the dozen gardeners that carefully managed and treated each specimen."

    old "Instead, they grew wildly and chaotically."
    new "Instead, they grew wildly and chaotically."

    old "But in a sense, they had their own beauty because of it."
    new "But in a sense, they had their own beauty because of it."

    old "Closer to how nature had intended for them to be."
    new "Closer to how nature had intended for them to be."

    old "More full of life, rather than the sterile world of the castle."
    new "More full of life, rather than the sterile world of the castle."

    old "She smiled as she leaned forward to pluck a few."
    new "She smiled as she leaned forward to pluck a few."

    old "No more than she needed."
    new "No more than she needed."

    old "When she returned to the house, she placed them in a vase on the table and went back to the work."
    new "When she returned to the house, she placed them in a vase on the table and went back to the work."

    old "Sweeping, cleaning, preparing dinner."
    new "Sweeping, cleaning, preparing dinner."

    old "Time, and the day, had a way of slipping through her fingers."
    new "Time, and the day, had a way of slipping through her fingers."

    old "Still working, Sarah idely looked up and saw Marius approach through the window."
    new "Still working, Sarah idely looked up and saw Marius approach through the window."

    old "She rushed out to meet him."
    new "She rushed out to meet him."

    old "The sun low and golden behind him, it marked his arrival almost as certainly as any clock would."
    new "The sun low and golden behind him, it marked his arrival almost as certainly as any clock would."

    old "He smiled and waved at her."
    new "He smiled and waved at her."

    old "She did the same back."
    new "She did the same back."

    old "Sarah noticed the heavy stains of sweat on his clothes. He had worked himself to the bone again."
    new "Sarah noticed the heavy stains of sweat on his clothes. He had worked himself to the bone again."

    old "Marius!"
    new "Marius!"

    old "You work too hard!"
    new "You work too hard!"

    old "He laughed as he stopped walking."
    new "He laughed as he stopped walking."

    old "He padded his clothes."
    new "He padded his clothes."

    old "This is nothing. I'm used to it."
    new "This is nothing. I'm used to it."

    old "Still. It can't be healthy to work this hard, every day."
    new "Still. It can't be healthy to work this hard, every day."

    old "You need to take care of yourself too. Not just everyone else."
    new "You need to take care of yourself too. Not just everyone else."

    old "Marius nodded and smiled."
    new "Marius nodded and smiled."

    old "But once the harvest season is over, things will get easier."
    new "But once the harvest season is over, things will get easier."

    old "Sarah nodded. She just hoped it was true, for his sake."
    new "Sarah nodded. She just hoped it was true, for his sake."

    old "Come in, I've got dinner ready."
    new "Come in, I've got dinner ready."

    old "Marius gestured at the horizon."
    new "Marius gestured at the horizon."

    old "Why eat inside when we got a view like this?"
    new "Why eat inside when we got a view like this?"

    old "Sarah hadn't even considered the option."
    new "Sarah hadn't even considered the option."

    old "Oh...you're right."
    new "Oh...you're right."

    old "You get the food, we'll eat it by the oak tree. Soun good."
    new "You get the food, we'll eat it by the oak tree. Soun good."

    old "Sarah nodded and excitedly retrieved the food."
    new "Sarah nodded and excitedly retrieved the food."

    old "When she approached the large oak tree, she saw Marius was already sitting in the alcove."
    new "When she approached the large oak tree, she saw Marius was already sitting in the alcove."

    old "The large tree had roots that wandered and twisted about, forming almost natural places to take rest in."
    new "The large tree had roots that wandered and twisted about, forming almost natural places to take rest in."

    old "Sarah sat down besides Marius on one of the particularly large roots."
    new "Sarah sat down besides Marius on one of the particularly large roots."

    old "She handed him the bowl of stew."
    new "She handed him the bowl of stew."

    old "Eagerly he took it."
    new "Eagerly he took it."

    old "Thanks, I'm starving."
    new "Thanks, I'm starving."

    old "He looked caught out again."
    new "He looked caught out again."

    old "You work that hard and you don't even eat a proper lunch?"
    new "You work that hard and you don't even eat a proper lunch?"

    old "I mean...I'm out so early, I just never..."
    new "I mean...I'm out so early, I just never..."

    old "Just, let me do it, okay?"
    new "Just, let me do it, okay?"

    old "I'll make you a lunch you can take out to the field when you go to work."
    new "I'll make you a lunch you can take out to the field when you go to work."

    old "She saw a strange flicker in his eyes."
    new "She saw a strange flicker in his eyes."

    old "Of course. It's no trouble for me. I wake early with you anyway."
    new "Of course. It's no trouble for me. I wake early with you anyway."

    old "Gosh, Sarah...you really are a life saver."
    new "Gosh, Sarah...you really are a life saver."

    old "She blushed and smiled."
    new "She blushed and smiled."

    old "Don't worry. It's the least I can do for what you've given me."
    new "Don't worry. It's the least I can do for what you've given me."

    old "Marius looked back at the house."
    new "Marius looked back at the house."

    old "Oh, yeah..."
    new "Oh, yeah..."

    old "How are you liking it so far, anyway?"
    new "How are you liking it so far, anyway?"

    old "It's great. Really. This town...I think it's exactly what I had been looking for."
    new "It's great. Really. This town...I think it's exactly what I had been looking for."

    old "Marius looked off into the distance."
    new "Marius looked off into the distance."

    old "You know, Sarah...you don't have to go any time soon."
    new "You know, Sarah...you don't have to go any time soon."

    old "I mean...you don't have to stay if you don't want to, obviously, but...I don't mind you staying over."
    new "I mean...you don't have to stay if you don't want to, obviously, but...I don't mind you staying over."

    old "Sarah smiled at him, and in his face she could see there wasn't a word he didn't mean."
    new "Sarah smiled at him, and in his face she could see there wasn't a word he didn't mean."

    old "Thank you, Marius. You've really been so kind to me."
    new "Thank you, Marius. You've really been so kind to me."

    old "The two of them continued to eat as they talked about their lives."
    new "The two of them continued to eat as they talked about their lives."

    old "Marius spoke openly about growing up in Gallow's Creek."
    new "Marius spoke openly about growing up in Gallow's Creek."

    old "Sarah, for her part, spoke it half veiled truths, trying to be as honest as she could be with him."
    new "Sarah, for her part, spoke it half veiled truths, trying to be as honest as she could be with him."

    old "Marius was hardly someone that would use the information about her life against her."
    new "Marius was hardly someone that would use the information about her life against her."

    old "But she feared what it might do to their relationship."
    new "But she feared what it might do to their relationship."

    old "Feared that if he knew she had been a Princess, he might grow distant with her."
    new "Feared that if he knew she had been a Princess, he might grow distant with her."

    old "Just when she yearned for closeness."
    new "Just when she yearned for closeness."

    old "Marius' voice was soft, tender."
    new "Marius' voice was soft, tender."

    old "In town..."
    new "In town..."

    old "He spoke slowly, as if considering every word."
    new "He spoke slowly, as if considering every word."

    old "In town, after the harvest comes in..."
    new "In town, after the harvest comes in..."

    old "Well, there is usually a harvest festival. People make food, music...dance."
    new "Well, there is usually a harvest festival. People make food, music...dance."

    old "If you'd like...I could take you there?"
    new "If you'd like...I could take you there?"

    old "I mean, show you around town. It would be a great chance to get to meet everyone."
    new "I mean, show you around town. It would be a great chance to get to meet everyone."

    old "Sarah saw the desperation in his eyes."
    new "Sarah saw the desperation in his eyes."

    old "He was not a man used to being vulnerable."
    new "He was not a man used to being vulnerable."

    old "Of course I'll go with you."
    new "Of course I'll go with you."

    old "It sounds like fun."
    new "It sounds like fun."

    old "Besides, I love to dance."
    new "Besides, I love to dance."

    old "Marius suddenly had a panicked expression on his face."
    new "Marius suddenly had a panicked expression on his face."

    old "I...I can't dance..."
    new "I...I can't dance..."

    old "She reached over and placed one hand on his arm."
    new "She reached over and placed one hand on his arm."

    old "You show me around town. I'll show you how to dance."
    new "You show me around town. I'll show you how to dance."

    old "Laughing, the two of them continued to eat together and tell stories of their lives."
    new "Laughing, the two of them continued to eat together and tell stories of their lives."

    old "It was a long time befor either of them realized how dark it had gotten."
    new "It was a long time befor either of them realized how dark it had gotten."

    old "They gathered up their plates and headed inside."
    new "They gathered up their plates and headed inside."

    old "Marius motioned at the flowers on the table."
    new "Marius motioned at the flowers on the table."

    old "Did you do that?"
    new "Did you do that?"

    old "You don't like them?"
    new "You don't like them?"

    old "No...they're great..."
    new "No...they're great..."

    old "There was something odd in his voice, but Sarah couldn't say what."
    new "There was something odd in his voice, but Sarah couldn't say what."

    old "The two parted ways, each retiring to their own room."
    new "The two parted ways, each retiring to their own room."

    old "Sarah laid down in her bed and looked up at the ceiling."
    new "Sarah laid down in her bed and looked up at the ceiling."

    old "In her mind, she replayed her conversation with Marius, over and over again, until she fell asleep."
    new "In her mind, she replayed her conversation with Marius, over and over again, until she fell asleep."

    old "Days came and went, each much the same."
    new "Days came and went, each much the same."

    old "Sarah settled into a comfortable pace."
    new "Sarah settled into a comfortable pace."

    old "Each day she imagined she was getting just a little better at all the house work."
    new "Each day she imagined she was getting just a little better at all the house work."

    old "And the house showed the results of her efforts."
    new "And the house showed the results of her efforts."

    old "The practical room where people slept had slowly become a home."
    new "The practical room where people slept had slowly become a home."

    old "Nearly a week had gone by when Marius reminded her that the harvest festival was in only a few days."
    new "Nearly a week had gone by when Marius reminded her that the harvest festival was in only a few days."

    old "The festival had almost slipped her minds."
    new "The festival had almost slipped her minds."

    old "Sarah spend what little free time she had, sowing a few adjustments to her dress."
    new "Sarah spend what little free time she had, sowing a few adjustments to her dress."

    old "On the night itself, she looked into the window, which was as close as they had to a mirror."
    new "On the night itself, she looked into the window, which was as close as they had to a mirror."

    old "Staring back at her was the perfect reflection of a farm girl."
    new "Staring back at her was the perfect reflection of a farm girl."

    old "Already so distant from the Princess she had long been."
    new "Already so distant from the Princess she had long been."

    old "How quick life re-made her, she wondered."
    new "How quick life re-made her, she wondered."

    old "Sarah plucked on the flowers from the vase."
    new "Sarah plucked on the flowers from the vase."

    old "This had been Marius' favorite."
    new "This had been Marius' favorite."

    old "Carefully, she placed into the strands of her hair, near her ear."
    new "Carefully, she placed into the strands of her hair, near her ear."

    old "She smiled at herself. Proud."
    new "She smiled at herself. Proud."

    old "Just then, the door flew open and Marius stumbled in."
    new "Just then, the door flew open and Marius stumbled in."

    old "When he saw her, his jaw dropped."
    new "When he saw her, his jaw dropped."

    old "You look incredible..."
    new "You look incredible..."

    old "In court, nobles played endless games of hiding their emotions and their intentions."
    new "In court, nobles played endless games of hiding their emotions and their intentions."

    old "Marius just said whatever laid on his heart."
    new "Marius just said whatever laid on his heart."

    old "I thought I'd put in a little extra effort for the festival."
    new "I thought I'd put in a little extra effort for the festival."

    old "But now I feel bad. I'm underdress."
    new "But now I feel bad. I'm underdress."

    old "Sarah walked up to him and looped her arm into his."
    new "Sarah walked up to him and looped her arm into his."

    old "She felt his body jolt from the slight touch of their skin."
    new "She felt his body jolt from the slight touch of their skin."

    old "You look great."
    new "You look great."

    old "Together, the two of them left the house and began to make their way towards the town's center."
    new "Together, the two of them left the house and began to make their way towards the town's center."

    old "Even from a distance, the many lights and people gathered, blazed in the dark of night like a bonfire."
    new "Even from a distance, the many lights and people gathered, blazed in the dark of night like a bonfire."

    old "As they came closer, she could hear the growing sounds of music and laughing."
    new "As they came closer, she could hear the growing sounds of music and laughing."

    old "It sounds fun."
    new "It sounds fun."

    old "Well, it's the best we can do, you know."
    new "Well, it's the best we can do, you know."

    old "I'm sure you're used to bigger things."
    new "I'm sure you're used to bigger things."

    old "Sarah patted his arm."
    new "Sarah patted his arm."

    old "Maybe, but I never had such good company."
    new "Maybe, but I never had such good company."

    old "She saw him blush at her remark."
    new "She saw him blush at her remark."

    old "As they ventured further into the town, Sarah saw a crowd begin to form."
    new "As they ventured further into the town, Sarah saw a crowd begin to form."

    old "Compared to where she had grown up in Rosanna, Gallow's Creek was tiny."
    new "Compared to where she had grown up in Rosanna, Gallow's Creek was tiny."

    old "But all packed together for the festival, even this small town suddenly seemed big."
    new "But all packed together for the festival, even this small town suddenly seemed big."

    old "Sarah watched as Marius greeted almost all of them as they walked through the town."
    new "Sarah watched as Marius greeted almost all of them as they walked through the town."

    old "Wow, you sure know a lot of people..."
    new "Wow, you sure know a lot of people..."

    old "Born here. Grew up here. Never gonna leave."
    new "Born here. Grew up here. Never gonna leave."

    old "You get to know a place, I guess."
    new "You get to know a place, I guess."

    old "Sarah saw his eyes glitter."
    new "Sarah saw his eyes glitter."

    old "In all her life, just about everyone she ever met was busy trying to get somewhere else."
    new "In all her life, just about everyone she ever met was busy trying to get somewhere else."

    old "Somewhere else in life, be it station or place."
    new "Somewhere else in life, be it station or place."

    old "But not him."
    new "But not him."

    old "All this time, he had been here, content with what he had, rather than losing himself in a struggle to get more."
    new "All this time, he had been here, content with what he had, rather than losing himself in a struggle to get more."

    old "He didn't want mansions or mountains of gold."
    new "He didn't want mansions or mountains of gold."

    old "If you offered him a crown, he'd probably hand it back."
    new "If you offered him a crown, he'd probably hand it back."

    old "He was perfectly happy where he was."
    new "He was perfectly happy where he was."

    old "I'm kind of jealous."
    new "I'm kind of jealous."

    old "She decided to be honest with him, or at least as much as she could be."
    new "She decided to be honest with him, or at least as much as she could be."

    old "You seem so...at home."
    new "You seem so...at home."

    old "Like you're exactly where you're supposed to be."
    new "Like you're exactly where you're supposed to be."

    old "I mean, I love every part of this land. I've worked it summer after summer."
    new "I mean, I love every part of this land. I've worked it summer after summer."

    old "And the people are good. Decent."
    new "And the people are good. Decent."

    old "But it's not all perfect, trust me."
    new "But it's not all perfect, trust me."

    old "Sarah frowned as they walked further through the festival."
    new "Sarah frowned as they walked further through the festival."

    old "His voice was suddenly brisk."
    new "His voice was suddenly brisk."

    old "Sarah pulled at his arm, forcing him to stop."
    new "Sarah pulled at his arm, forcing him to stop."

    old "No. Tell me what you meant."
    new "No. Tell me what you meant."

    old "Marius suddenly looked away, as if afraid of making eye contact."
    new "Marius suddenly looked away, as if afraid of making eye contact."

    old "It's just..."
    new "It's just..."

    old "This town is small. There aren't a lot of people."
    new "This town is small. There aren't a lot of people."

    old "That's good...but it's also..."
    new "That's good...but it's also..."

    old "I don't know...it can be lonely."
    new "I don't know...it can be lonely."

    old "Sarah saw the hurt in his eyes."
    new "Sarah saw the hurt in his eyes."

    old "Lonely...I can understand that."
    new "Lonely...I can understand that."

    old "It's just...it didn't used to be like that."
    new "It's just...it didn't used to be like that."

    old "Before, when it was me, my dad and my mom, it was all perfect."
    new "Before, when it was me, my dad and my mom, it was all perfect."

    old "And I always dreamed of having something like that myself, you know, a family?"
    new "And I always dreamed of having something like that myself, you know, a family?"

    old "But after mom died, my dad he...I don't know, he turned colder."
    new "But after mom died, my dad he...I don't know, he turned colder."

    old "And as he got older, I had to pick up more of the work."
    new "And as he got older, I had to pick up more of the work."

    old "But it was just enough to keep us fed and keep the house over our head."
    new "But it was just enough to keep us fed and keep the house over our head."

    old "I was focussed on surviving."
    new "I was focussed on surviving."

    old "So by the time I looked up and thought about a family of my own, most of the women in town had already settled."
    new "So by the time I looked up and thought about a family of my own, most of the women in town had already settled."

    old "And in this place, if you miss the boat...well, there ain't much second chances."
    new "And in this place, if you miss the boat...well, there ain't much second chances."

    old "I think I can understand."
    new "I think I can understand."

    old "I've been the same, in a lot of ways."
    new "I've been the same, in a lot of ways."

    old "Running. Surviving. Always so busy that I hardly have time to think of anything else."
    new "Running. Surviving. Always so busy that I hardly have time to think of anything else."

    old "I guess...if you keep that up for too long...you're always so focussed on the day to day, you forget to think about the bigger picture."
    new "I guess...if you keep that up for too long...you're always so focussed on the day to day, you forget to think about the bigger picture."

    old "Gods, I was so afraid of telling you this."
    new "Gods, I was so afraid of telling you this."

    old "Why would you be afraid?"
    new "Why would you be afraid?"

    old "Well...I thought you'd think poorly of me. That I offered you a place to stay, just because you're..."
    new "Well...I thought you'd think poorly of me. That I offered you a place to stay, just because you're..."

    old "He stumbled on the last few words."
    new "He stumbled on the last few words."

    old "Because what?"
    new "Because what?"

    old "Because you're so pretty."
    new "Because you're so pretty."

    old "Sarah blushed at his sudden honesty."
    new "Sarah blushed at his sudden honesty."

    old "She wasn't a fool. She knew how he looked at her."
    new "She wasn't a fool. She knew how he looked at her."

    old "But with him, she didn't mind as much."
    new "But with him, she didn't mind as much."

    old "Most men had eyes that were filled with malice and lust."
    new "Most men had eyes that were filled with malice and lust."

    old "His were love."
    new "His were love."

    old "She reached out and touched his arm."
    new "She reached out and touched his arm."

    old "With her fingers, she could feel the hard surface of his skin, muscled from a life of working the land."
    new "With her fingers, she could feel the hard surface of his skin, muscled from a life of working the land."

    old "Don't worry, Marius."
    new "Don't worry, Marius."

    old "I could never think poorly of you."
    new "I could never think poorly of you."

    old "You've shown me a kindness when nobody else will."
    new "You've shown me a kindness when nobody else will."

    old "I'll always be grateful for that."
    new "I'll always be grateful for that."

    old "He smiled at her again, with all the same genuine intent that defined him."
    new "He smiled at her again, with all the same genuine intent that defined him."

    old "And Sarah felt a spark of something in her chest."
    new "And Sarah felt a spark of something in her chest."

    old "Together, the two of them continued to explore the festival."
    new "Together, the two of them continued to explore the festival."

    old "One of the families from a nearby farmstead had a stand where they were frying something."
    new "One of the families from a nearby farmstead had a stand where they were frying something."

    old "Sarah lingered near the stand for a moment."
    new "Sarah lingered near the stand for a moment."

    old "You want one?"
    new "You want one?"

    old "Oh, no don't worry about it. I don't have any money."
    new "Oh, no don't worry about it. I don't have any money."

    old "Before she could even properly refute him, Marius had already reached into his pocket and pulled out a few coins."
    new "Before she could even properly refute him, Marius had already reached into his pocket and pulled out a few coins."

    old "He handed the money to the stall owners, and a minute later, they received the fried food."
    new "He handed the money to the stall owners, and a minute later, they received the fried food."

    old "They continued to explore the festival ground together whilst eating."
    new "They continued to explore the festival ground together whilst eating."

    old "Wow, this is really good."
    new "Wow, this is really good."

    old "Yeah, I used to be crazy about them."
    new "Yeah, I used to be crazy about them."

    old "When I worked my first season on the land, I had so much money I didn't know what to do with myself."
    new "When I worked my first season on the land, I had so much money I didn't know what to do with myself."

    old "I bought like two dozen of those things and ate them all."
    new "I bought like two dozen of those things and ate them all."

    old "Spend the next morning paying for it."
    new "Spend the next morning paying for it."

    old "Oh no!"
    new "Oh no!"

    old "Sarah laughed along with him."
    new "Sarah laughed along with him."

    old "It's true."
    new "It's true."

    old "Couldn't eat the things for a few years after that."
    new "Couldn't eat the things for a few years after that."

    old "Sarah took another bite and pledged to only eat the one."
    new "Sarah took another bite and pledged to only eat the one."

    old "Thank you again, for buying me one."
    new "Thank you again, for buying me one."

    old "Sarah pointed towards a nearby log."
    new "Sarah pointed towards a nearby log."

    old "You mind if we take a break? My feet are killing me."
    new "You mind if we take a break? My feet are killing me."

    old "Together, the two of them sat down on the log, a small distance away from the festival."
    new "Together, the two of them sat down on the log, a small distance away from the festival."

    old "You like it so far?"
    new "You like it so far?"

